 <table-wrap-foot class="table-wrap-foot">
  <fn id="gcb13967-note-0001" class="fn">
   <label class="label">a</label>
   <p class="p">The classification into West, North and East is ours, based on geographic location which roughly also corresponds with growing conditions (East is cooler than West; North is semiarid, warmer than East but cooler than West).</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="gcb13967-note-0002" class="fn">
   <label class="label">b</label>
   <p class="p">Total harvested area based on SPAM2005 (You et al., 
    <xref rid="gcb13967-bib-0075" ref-type="ref" class="xref">2014</xref>). Note if in a country two rice crops are harvested per year, then harvested area is 2× the physical area. Especially in irrigated systems double rice cropping is found.
   </p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="gcb13967-note-0003" class="fn">
   <label class="label">c</label>
   <p class="p">The last two columns show the total number of sites (point locations central in key rice producing areas) used in the simulations.</p>
  </fn>
